Preheat your oven to 200°C. Take the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} out of the fridge
and pop onto a #plate{}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!).
Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, and
sprinkle on the @smoked paprika{1} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss
to coat in the oil, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, chop the @medium tomato{2} into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}
(or use a #garlic press{}). Take a quarter of the @wild rocket{40%g} and finely chop (we will
use this as a herb for the salsa). Pop the rest of the rocket into a #bowl{} with half of the
tomatoes.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. Add the
@chorizo{60%g} and cook for ~{2%minutes} until the chorizo starts to release its fragrant
oil. Add the garlic and remaining tomatoes. Cook for a minute more. Remove from the heat
and stir in the @red wine vinegar{12} and @olive oil{}. Transfer to a small bowl, allow to
cool for a minute and then stir in the chopped rocket. Salsa made! Keep the pan.

When the wedges have 10 mins left, wipe out the frying pan and return to high heat with a
drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. When
the oil is hot, lay the steaks in the pan and brown for ~{1%minute} on each side. Once
browned, lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side.

> TIP: This will cook the steak to medium rare - if you like yours less rare just cook for
> 1-2 mins more.

While the steaks cook, do any washing up that needs doing and get ready to serve. Dress
the rocket and tomato salad with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and toss to coat. Arrange on
your plates. When the steaks are cooked, transfer to your #chopping board{} and allow to
rest for a couple of mins.

Pop the wedges onto your plates next to the rocket salad. Thinly slice the steak and
arrange alongside. Spoon the salsa over the steak. Enjoy!